 law barrister\n\n==Military leaders==\n\n===Indian Air Force===\n* [[Marshal]] of the Air Force [[Arjan Singh]], former Chief, [[Indian Air Force]].<ref>[http://www.mapsofindia.com/who-is-who/defence/marshal-arjan-singh.html Marshal Arjan Singh]. Mapsofindia.com. Retrieved on 2010-12-14.</ref>\n* [[Air Chief Marshal]] [[Dilbagh Singh]], former Chief, [[Indian Air Force]].\n*[[Air Chief Marshal]] [[Birender Singh Dhanoa]], former chief, [[Indian Air Force]].\n\n===Air Marshal of Air Force===\n*[[Harjit Singh Arora]]\n*[[Trilochan Singh Brar]]\n*[[Kulwant Singh Gill]]\n*[[Jasjit Singh (IAF officer)|Jasjit Singh]]\n*[[Jagjeet Singh]]\n\n===Indian army===\n* Gen. [[Joginder Jaswant Singh]], former Chief, [[Indian Army]].\n* [[Bikram Singh (general)|Gen. Bikram Singh]], former Chief, [[Indian Army]].\n* [[Bikram Singh (soldier)|Lt. Gen. Bikram Singh]], G O C, XV Corps,1960\u201363\n*[[Joginder Singh Dhillon]]\n\n==Military Gallantry Award Winners==\n\n===British Indian Army===\n\n====Victoria Cross====\n*[[Ishar Singh]] was the first [[Sikh]] to receive the [[Victoria Cross]]\n*[[Nand Singh]]\n*[[Gian Singh]]\n*[[Parkash Singh]]\n*[[Karamjeet Singh Judge]]\n\n===Indian Armed Forces===\n\n====Param Veer Chakra====\n*[[Nirmal Jit Singh Sekhon]], only Indian Air Force officer to be awarded Param Vir Chakra\n*[[Subedar]] [[Bana Singh]]\n*[[Karam Singh]]\n*[[Joginder Singh Sahnan]]\n\n====Mahavir Chakra====\n*[[Dewan Ranjit Rai]], first Indian to receive Mahavir Chakra \n*Brigadier [[Rajendra Singh (Brigadier)|Rajinder Singh]]\n*[[Rajinder Singh Sparrow]]\n*[[Sant Singh]]\n*[[Ranjit Singh Dyal]]\n*Brigadier [[Kuldip Singh Chandpuri]],  known for his heroic leadership in the famous [[Battle of Longewala]]\n*Major General [[Kulwant Singh Pannu]]\n\n== See also ==\n\n* [[List of British Sikhs]]\n\n==References==\n\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Sikhism}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sikhs}}\n[[Category:Lists of people by belief]]\n[[Category:Sikhism-related lists]]\n[[Category:Sikhs|*List]]\n", "n